{
  "answer": "In Allama Iqbal's *Bang-E-Dara*, the poem \"Insaan\" in Part 2 (Chapter 14) concludes on a note of existential isolation and bitterness about the human condition.[^1] By contrast, the poem \"Insaan\" in Part 3 (Chapter 12) celebrates humanity's inherent power, wisdom, and capacity for transformation.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, \"Insaan\" [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/14-insaan/translation/#p-62d764).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, \"Insaan\" [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/12-insaan/translation/#p-587d8c).",
